  "stdout": "\u25cf Read word-game-infra-specialist.agent.md\n  \u2502 .github/agents/word-game-infra-specialist.agent.md\n  \u2514 69 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read word-game-infra-critic.agent.md\n  \u2502 .github/agents/word-game-infra-critic.agent.md\n  \u2514 31 lines read\n\n\u25cf Search (glob)\n  \u2502 \"work/todo/*\"\n  \u2514 1 file found\n\nI\u2019m pulling the request and the surrounding Terraform/requirements context, then I\u2019ll implement the change and run the repo validation gate.\n\n\u2717 Read main.tf\n  \u2514 Path does not exist\n\n\u2717 Read platform-guardrails.yml\n  \u2502 .requirements/platform-guardrails.yml\n  \u2514 Path does not exist\n\n\u2717 Read deployment-updates.yml\n  \u2502 .requirements/deployment-updates.yml\n  \u2514 Path does not exist\n\n\u25cf Read add-cosmos-private-dns-zone.yml\n  \u2502 work/todo/add-cosmos-private-dns-zone.yml\n  \u2514 64 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read variables.tf\n  \u2514 98 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read outputs.tf\n  \u2514 48 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read cosmos.tf\n  \u2514 72 lines read\n\n\u25cf List directory .contracts/\n  \u2514 2 files found\n\n\u25cf Read log.md\n  \u2502 .decisions/log.md\n  \u2514 20 lines read\n\n\u25cf Search (glob)\n  \u2502 \".requirements/*\"\n  \u2514 No matches found\n\n\u25cf Search (glob)\n  \u2502 \"work/*\"\n  \u2514 No matches found\n\n\u25cf Search (glob)\n  \u2502 \".contracts/*\"\n  \u2514 2 files found\n\n\u25cf Search (glob)\n  \u2502 \"*.tf\"\n  \u2514 14 files found\n\nI\u2019ve confirmed there\u2019s one queued item. Next I\u2019m checking the Cosmos/VNet wiring and contract schema so the fix is additive and matches the repository\u2019s conventions.\n\n\u25cf Read locals.tf\n  \u2514 49 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read cosmos-schema.yml\n  \u2502 .contracts/cosmos-schema.yml\n  \u2514 76 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read network-flows.yml\n  \u2502 .contracts/network-flows.yml\n  \u2514 75 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read versions.tf\n  \u2514 18 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read providers.tf\n  \u2514 18 lines read\n\n\u25cf Read networking.tf\n  \u2514 225 lines read\n\n\u25cf Search (grep)\n  \u2502 \"private_dns_zone_virtual_network_link\"\n  \u2514 2 lines found\n\n\u25cf Search (grep)\n  \u2502 \"azurerm_private_dns_zone\"\n  \u2514 9 lines found\n\n\u25cf Search (grep)\n  \u2502 \"private_dns_zone_resource_ids\"\n  \u2514 2 lines found\n\n\u25cf Search (grep)\n  \u2502 \"private_endpoints = \\{\"\n  \u2514 4 lines found\n\n\u25cf Read container-apps.tf\n  \u2514 111 lines read\n\nI\u2019ve got enough context to start the specialist pass. I\u2019m delegating the Cosmos DNS fix now, then I\u2019ll review it against the critic checklist and the Terraform gate.\n\n\u25cf Task(claude-sonnet-4.6) Implement Cosmos private DNS zone\n  \u2514 Agent started in background with agent_id: cosmos-private-dns-fix. You'l...\n\n\u25cf Check repo status (shell)\n  \u2502 git -C /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra status --short --branch\n  \u2514 3 lines\u2026\n\n\u25cf Edit\n  \u2514 Create ~/.copilot/session-state/1d7c9ea7-6f22-44c8-9b05-25857bd07d49/plan.md\n\nI have all the context needed. Now I'll make the three changes to `cosmos.tf` in a single pass, following the `container-apps.tf` pattern exactly.File looks correct. Now run the full validation gate.All three gate steps passed with exit code 0. Here's a summary:\n\n---\n\n## Changes made \u2014 `cosmos.tf` only\n\n### 1. Added `azurerm_private_dns_zone.cosmos` (new resource)\n```hcl\nresource \"azurerm_private_dns_zone\" \"cosmos\" {\n  name                = \"privatelink.documents.azure.com\"\n  resource_group_name = azurerm_resource_group.main.name\n  tags                = local.tags\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Added `azurerm_private_dns_zone_virtual_network_link.cosmos` (new resource)\n```hcl\nresource \"azurerm_private_dns_zone_virtual_network_link\" \"cosmos\" {\n  name                  = \"${local.prefix}-cosmos-dns-link\"\n  resource_group_name   = azurerm_resource_group.main.name\n  private_dns_zone_name = azurerm_private_dns_zone.cosmos.name\n  virtual_network_id    = azurerm_virtual_network.main.id\n  registration_enabled  = false\n  tags                  = local.tags\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Updated `module \"cosmos\"` private_endpoints block (attribute addition only)\n```hcl\n# before\nprivate_endpoints = {\n  \"cosmos\" = {\n    subnet_resource_id = azurerm_subnet.private_endpoints.id\n    subresource_name   = \"Sql\"\n  }\n}\n\n# after\nprivate_endpoints = {\n  \"cosmos\" = {\n    subnet_resource_id            = azurerm_subnet.private_endpoints.id\n    subresource_name              = \"Sql\"\n    private_dns_zone_resource_ids = [azurerm_private_dns_zone.cosmos.id]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Validation gate results\n| Step | Result |\n|------|--------|\n| `terraform fmt -check -recursive` | \u2705 Exit 0 \u2014 no formatting issues |\n| `terraform init -backend=false -input=false` | \u2705 Exit 0 \u2014 all providers resolved from lock file |\n| `terraform validate` | \u2705 Exit 0 \u2014 `Success! The configuration is valid.` |\n\nNo other files were touched. The changes are purely additive \u2014 the two new resources (`azurerm_private_dns_zone.cosmos` and `azurerm_private_dns_zone_virtual_network_link.cosmos`) will be `+ add` in any subsequent `terraform plan`, and the `private_dns_zone_resource_ids` wiring tells the AVM module to register the NIC DNS record in the zone, which resolves the Forbidden/public-IP routing issue described in the todo.\u25cf Read (Task agent \u2014 Implement Cosmos private DNS zone)\n  \u2514 idle\n\nThe implementation is in place. I\u2019m checking the resulting diff and then I\u2019ll run the repo gate myself before I finalize the item.\n\n\u25cf Read cosmos.tf\n  \u2514 88 lines read\n\n\u25cf Show cosmos.tf diff (shell)\n  \u2502 git -C /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra diff -- cosmos.tf\n  \u2514 36 lines\u2026\n\n\u25cf Run terraform validation gate (shell)\n  \u2502 terraform fmt -check -recursive && terraform init -backend=false\n  \u2502 -input=false && terraform validate\n  \u2514 25 lines\u2026\n\nI\u2019ve got the Terraform gate green. I\u2019m running the critic pass now against the actual diff, including security review, before I close the item out.\n\n\u25cf Code-review(claude-sonnet-4.6) Review Cosmos DNS change\n  \u2514 Agent started in background with agent_id: cosmos-dns-review. You'll be ...\n\n\u25cf Security-review(claude-sonnet-4.6) Security review Cosmos DNS change\n  \u2514 Agent started in background with agent_id: cosmos-dns-security-review. Y...\n\nNo security vulnerabilities found in the reviewed changes.\n\nThe diff is clean against all relevant threat categories:\n\n- **DNS zone name** (`privatelink.documents.azure.com`) is the correct canonical Azure private DNS zone for Cosmos DB SQL API. It exactly matches the container-apps pattern already in the codebase.\n- **`registration_enabled = false`** is correct. Enabling auto-registration on a private link zone would pollute it with VM hostnames and is inappropriate here; `false` is the right setting.\n- **Zone scope**: The private DNS zone is linked only to `azurerm_virtual_network.main` (the spoke VNet). The hub VNet has no link, which is correct and slightly more conservative \u2014 hub resources cannot resolve or reach Cosmos over private DNS unless a hub-side link is explicitly added.\n- **Cosmos access controls** (unchanged but confirmed present in the diff context): `public_network_access_enabled = false` and `local_authentication_disabled = true` remain set; the private endpoint is the sole connectivity path.\n- **AVM module version** (`~> 0.9`) is pinned to a patch-locked range from an officially maintained Azure namespace \u2014 consistent with existing module pinning in this repo and within acceptable supply chain practices.\n- **No injection, credential, or data exposure surfaces** are introduced \u2014 this change is pure infrastructure wiring with no dynamic/user-controlled values.\u25cf Read (Security-review agent \u2014 Security review Cosmos DNS change)\n  \u2514 idle\n\nNo significant issues found in the reviewed changes.\n\nThe diff is complete and functionally correct:\n\n- **DNS zone name** `privatelink.documents.azure.com` is confirmed correct for Cosmos DB SQL API \u2014 matches the AVM module's own example at `.terraform/modules/cosmos/examples/private-endpoints-managed-dns-records/main.tf:67`.\n- **AVM wiring** is correct: `private_endpoints_manage_dns_zone_group` defaults to `true` in the module, so supplying `private_dns_zone_resource_ids` will cause the module to create the `private_dns_zone_group` block in the PE and auto-register the A record.\n- **VNet link** correctly targets `azurerm_virtual_network.main.id` with `registration_enabled = false`.\n- **Dependency ordering** is implicit via the resource ID reference \u2014 no manual `depends_on` needed.\n- **Pattern consistency**: identical structure to the existing `container_apps` DNS zone/link in `container-apps.tf`.\n- **Hub-spoke DNS**: the VNet uses Azure-provided DNS (no custom `dns_servers`), so the spoke-local zone link resolves correctly. The optional hub peering (`count = var.hub_vnet_name != \"\" ? 1 : 0`) mirrors the existing unconditional DNS zone pattern already established by `container-apps.tf` \u2014 no regression introduced here.\n\nOne pre-existing condition unrelated to this diff: `subresource_name = \"Sql\"` (mixed case) whereas the AVM module's own docs and examples specify `\"SQL\"`. The Azure provider accepts both (case-insensitive at the REST layer), and `terraform validate` passes, so this is not a blocking issue and was not introduced by this change.\n\nThe change is acceptable to merge.\u25cf Read (Code-review agent \u2014 Review Cosmos DNS change)\n  \u2514 idle\n\n\u25cf Search (glob)\n  \u2502 \"work/*\"\n  \u2514 No matches found\n\n\u25cf List work directories (shell)\n  \u2502 cd /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra && ls -la work && ls -la\n  \u2502 work/todo\n  \u2514 11 lines\u2026\n\n\u25cf Check git status (shell)\n  \u2502 cd /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra && git status --short\n  \u2514 3 lines\u2026\n\n\u25cf List work status dirs (shell)\n  \u2502 cd /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra && ls -la work/done && ls -la\n  \u2502 work/ready-for-review\n  \u2514 11 lines\u2026\n\n\u2717 Read 004-remove-github-actions-cicd.md\n  \u2502 work/done/004-remove-github-actions-cicd.md\n  \u2514 Path does not exist\n\n\u25cf Show work items (shell)\n  \u2502 cd /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra && printf '%s\n  \u2502 ' work/done/* work/ready-for-review/* | sed 's#^#- #'\n  \u2514 5 lines\u2026\n\n\u25cf Inspect work item formats (shell)\n  \u2502 cd /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra && sed -n '1,40p'\n  \u2502 work/ready-for-review/004-remove-github-actions-cicd.md && printf '\\n---\\n'\n  \u2502 && sed -n '1,40p' work/done/001-full-infrastructure.md\n  \u2514 83 lines\u2026\n\nThe change is clean, so I\u2019m just filing the completed request into `work/done/` and then I\u2019ll close out the queue.\n\n\u25cf Move request to done (shell)\n  \u2502 cd /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra && mv\n  \u2502 work/todo/add-cosmos-private-dns-zone.yml\n  \u2502 work/done/add-cosmos-private-dns-zone.yml\n  \u2514 1 line\u2026\n\n\u25cf Verify final git status (shell)\n  \u2502 cd /home/mike/source/word-game/word-game-infra && git status --short\n  \u2514 3 lines\u2026\n\nImplemented the Cosmos private DNS fix in `cosmos.tf`: added `privatelink.documents.azure.com`, linked it to the VNet, and wired the Cosmos AVM private endpoint to use the zone. The Terraform gate passed (`fmt`, `init`, `validate`), and the request was moved to `work/done/add-cosmos-private-dns-zone.yml`.\n\n",
